docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Uruguay, Nov. 28 (UP) -- The Colorado party emerged victorious in today's general elections. Complete official returns from the capital area showed that the Colorado factions headed by former President Luis Batlle Berres will get six of the nine seats in the National Council.

docs.lead_paragraph: A steady stream of offerings of British sterling every day of last week knocked that unit off to $2.78 15/15, lowest since October, 1952. Week's highest was $2.79 5/16, and Friday's final of $2.78 31/32 recorded a loss of 11/32 cent from the preceding week. Forwards were similarly affected.
